      {
         "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Nearby migrations, but...</b><br /><br />Human occupation of Europe occurred before human occupation of Japan (Nippon koku or Nihon koku, 日本国) (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).<br /><br />The occupation of the Americas (<i>Abya Yala</i>) occurred after the arrival of humanity in Japan (Nippon koku or Nihon koku, 日本国) (<htcite2>).<br /><br />What do these events have in common?<br /><br />What is different about them?</div></div></center></p>",
