                     "external_family_file": false,
                     "name": "Unknown",
                     "history": [
                        {
                           "text": "Despite the diversification of the Japanese population over time due to migrations, in Hokkaido, until the 19th century according to the Gregorian calendar, there were still people with physical characteristics from Jōmon times (縄文) (<htcite0>). This indicates population continuity across generations.",
                           "source": [
                              {
                                 "type": 1,
